{{Infobox venue | name = Bafra Sports Hall | nickname = | native_name = Bafra Kapalı Spor Salonu | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = Turkey | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the sports hall in Turkey. | pushpin_label_position = | address = Fatih Mah., Sedde Yolu 2. Sok. | location = [[Bafra]], [[Samsun province|Samsun]], Turkey | coordinates = {{coord|41|34|39|N|35|53|43|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = May 5, 2012 | built = | opened = {{start date and age|2013|12|20}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 2,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = {{ubl|2008 Balkan U-19 Badminton Championship |2015 Balkan Kungfu Wushu Championship |2015 BInternational Wushu Championship |[[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] }} | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''Bafra Sports Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Bafra Kapalı Spor Salonu}}) is a multi-purpose [[indoor arena|indoor sport venue]] located in [[Bafra]] district of [[Samsun Province]], northern Turkey.
The sports hall is situated in Fatih Mah., Sedde Yolu 2. Sok. in Bafra. It hosts badminton, wrestling, taekwondo and Wushu events.<ref name="ss"/> Groundbreaking for the construction of the sports hall took place on May 5, 2012.<ref name="b2000tv"/> It was opened on December 20, 2013.<ref name="bh1"/> The venue has a seating capacity for 2,000 spectators, including 100 for [[Very important person|VIP]], 100 for media members, 100 for accredited sportspeople and 80 for physically handicapped people.<ref name="d"/>
==International events hosted== The 2008 Balkan U19 Badminton Championship was the first international sports event hosted by the old Bafra Sport Hall.<ref name="s55"/> In 2015, the Balkan Kungfu Wushu Championship,<ref name="m1"/> and International Wushu Championship were held in the sport hall.<ref name="m2"/> The venue will host badminton events of the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]].<ref name="d"/>
