{{Expand Polish|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Bogdan Tuszyński | image = Tuszynski Bogdan.jpg | alt = | caption = Tuszyński in August 2007 | birth_name = Bogdan Romuald Tuszyński | birth_date = {{Birth date|1932|07|04|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Łódź]], Poland | death_date = {{Death date and age|2017|01|01|1932|07|04|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Warsaw]], Poland | nationality = Polish | other_names = | occupation = Journalist, reporter, historian | years_active = 1951&ndash;2017 | known_for = | children = 3; including [[Agata Tuszyńska]] | notable_works = }}
'''Bogdan Romuald Tuszyński''' (4 July 1932 &ndash; 1 January 2017) was a Polish sports journalist, reporter and historian. He was best known for his sports report ''Studio S-13'' of the [[Polskie Radio]], beginning in 1970. Born in [[Łódź]], he began his career as an editor of ''[[Przegląd Sportowy]]'' (1951&ndash;1952), before moving to Polskie Radio in 1953, departing from the radio broadcaster in 1981. He also reported on the [[Peace Race]] annually. He published approximately thirty books between 1975 and 2009.
For his services to Polish sports journalist, Tuszyński was awarded the [[Order of Polonia Restituta]] and the [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Cross of Merit]].<ref name=death/>
Tuszyński died following a long illness on 1 January 2017 in [[Warsaw]] at the age of 84.<ref name=death>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dzienniklodzki.pl/wiadomosci/a/zmarl-bogdan-tuszynski,11645285/|title=Zmarł Bogdan Tuszyński|author=Kuczmera, Dariusz|language=Polish|work=Dziennik Łódzk|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=2 January 2017}}</ref>
