[[File:Holmenkollen with visitors centre.jpg|thumb|Holmenkollen ski jump]] [[File:Ski Museum in Oslo 1925.jpg|thumb|Original Ski Museum building in 1925, then located in the [[Frognerseteren]] neighbourhood]] [[File:Holmenkollen, Oslo 20150725 201234.jpg|thumb|Display of skis at Holmenkollen Ski Museum]]
'''Holmenkollen Ski Museum''' ({{lang-no|Skimuseet i Holmenkollen}}) is located at the base of the [[Holmenkollen ski jump]] in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]]. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.visitoslo.com/no/produkt/?TLp=496475|title= Holmenkollen skimuseum & hopptårn|publisher= Oslo Visitor Centre |accessdate= September 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Skimuseet_i_Holmenkollen|title =Skimuseet i Holmenkollen |publisher= lokalhistoriewiki.no|accessdate= September 1, 2017}}</ref>
The Ski Museum was founded in 1923 and is the world's oldest [[ski]] museum. The initiator of the museum was the architect [[Hjalmar Welhaven]]. His private collection formed the foundation of the antique and historic skis on display at the museum. Until 1951, the collection was housed in a building in the Oslo neighborhood of [[Frognerseteren]]. In connection with the rebuilding of Holmenkollbakken in 1951, the museum collection was moved to new premises at [[Holmenkollbakken]]. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Hjalmar_Welhaven|title= Hjalmar Welhaven|publisher= lokalhistoriewiki.no |accessdate= September 1, 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url= https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Frognerseteren |title =Frognerseteren|publisher= lokalhistoriewiki.no|accessdate= September 1, 2017}}</ref>
The museum contains 4,000 years of skiing history, starting with rock carvings dating from the [[Stone Age]]. It also displays skiers and skis from the [[Viking Age]]. Additionally it displays equipment used in the polar expeditions of both [[Fridtjof Nansen]] and [[Roald Amundsen]]. The Ski Museum is owned and operated by Skiforeningen. This association is responsible for the organization of sports, activities and events in Holmenkollen National Park. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://snl.no/Holmenkollbakken|title= Holmenkollbakken|publisher = Store norske leksikon |author= Rolf Bryhn|accessdate= January 1, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.skiforeningen.no/en/holmenkollen/skimuseet/|title =The Ski Museum |publisher= skiforeningen|accessdate= September 1, 2017}}</ref>
