{{LNB Pro A awards}} The '''LNB Pro A MVP''' is the [[MVP]] [[LNB Pro A Awards|award]] of the [[French basketball league system|top-tier level]] men's professional [[sports club|club]] [[basketball]] league in [[France]], the [[LNB Pro A]]. Maxi-Basket holds the vote, and calls it the referendum.
==Player of the Year awards (before 1983)== [[File:Alain Gilles.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Alain Gilles]] was a 3 time Player of the Year (1965, 1967, 1968).]] Before 1983, the title of the best player in the league was sometimes assigned by a panel of [[sports journalists|journalists]], but the charts are incomplete.
*[[Jean Degros]] ([[ASC Denain-Voltaire PH|Denain]]) was voted the best player of the year in the 1962–63 season. *[[Alain Gilles]] ([[ASVEL Lyon-Villeurbanne|ASVEL]]) was voted the best player of the year in the 1964–65, 1966–67, and 1967–68 seasons. *[[Michel Le Ray]] ([[ABC Nantes]]) was voted the best player of the year in the 1965–66 season. *[[Pierre Galle]] ([[AS Berck]]) was voted the best player of the year in the 1972–73 and 1973–74 seasons.
==Two awards (1983–2014)== Between 1983 and 2005, the monthly Maxi-Basket conducted a vote of the players and [[head coach|head]] [[basketball coach|coaches]] of the league. Since 2005, the coaches and [[captain (sports)|captains]] of the [[LNB Pro A]] clubs, and a panel of fifty [[sports journalist|journalists]] are asked to vote.<ref>[http://www.lnb-media.net/download/LNBNEWS9.pdf LNB-Media.net LNB News.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723193000/http://www.lnb-media.net/download/LNBNEWS9.pdf |date=2011-07-23 }}</ref>
Since the [[2014–15 LNB Pro A season]], the MVP award is a single unified award. Prior to that, it was divided into two separate awards, one for French players, and one for non-French players.
