{{IIHFnation |IIHFnation = Nepal |bg_color = red |text_color = white |logo_image = |organization = Nepal Ice Hockey Association |code = NEP |founded = June 17, 2014 |joined = May 20, 2016 |president = Lok Bahadur Shahi }} The '''Nepal Ice Hockey Association''' ('''NIHA''') ({{lang-ne|नेपाल आइस हक्की संघ}}) is the governing body of [[ice hockey]] in [[Nepal]].
==History== The Nepal Ice Hockey Association was founded on June 17, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nepalnews.com/index.php/sports-archive/36718-nepal-ice-hockey-association-comes-into-being|title=Nepal Ice Hockey Association comes into being|date=2014-07-16|website=nepalnews.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thehockeyhouse.net/international-hockey/nepal-country-famous-for-mount-everest-announces-ice-hockey-association/|title=Nepal, Country Famous For Mount Everest, Announces Ice Hockey Association|date=2014-07-16|website=thehockeyhouse.net}}</ref> The NIHA consists of 16 members, including Lok Bahadur Shahi, a former national footballer who is engaged in various other social activities. Nepal joined the [[International Ice Hockey Federation]] (IIHF) on May 20, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iihfworlds2016.com/en/news/iihf-grows-in-asia/|title=IIHF grows in Asia|date=2016-05-21|website=iihf.com}}</ref>
