{{Infobox country at games | IAAF = PRK | fedname = | year = 2017 | games = World Championships in Athletics | location = [[London]] | competitors = 3 | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | rank = | appearances = * [[North Korea at the 1983 World Championships in Athletics|1983]] * [[North Korea at the 1987 World Championships in Athletics|1987]] * [[North Korea at the 1991 World Championships in Athletics|1991]] * [[North Korea at the 1993 World Championships in Athletics|1993]] * [[North Korea at the 1995 World Championships in Athletics|1995]] * [[North Korea at the 1997 World Championships in Athletics|1997]] * [[North Korea at the 1999 World Championships in Athletics|1999]] * [[North Korea at the 2001 World Championships in Athletics|2001]] * [[North Korea at the 2003 World Championships in Athletics|2003]] * [[North Korea at the 2005 World Championships in Athletics|2005]] * [[North Korea at the 2007 World Championships in Athletics|2007]] * [[North Korea at the 2009 World Championships in Athletics|2009]] * [[North Korea at the 2011 World Championships in Athletics|2011]] *[[North Korea at the 2013 World Championships in Athletics|2013]] *[[North Korea at the 2015 World Championships in Athletics|2015]] * '''2017''' | previous = [[North Korea at the 2015 World Championships in Athletics|2015]] | next = [[North Korea at the 2019 World Championships in Athletics|2019]] | website = }}
[[North Korea]] competed at the [[2017 World Championships in Athletics]] held in [[London]], [[Great Britain]], from 4–13 August 2017. The country was represented by three athletes, all of them runners taking part in the [[2017 World Championships in Athletics – Women's marathon|women's marathon event]] on 6 August. [[Kim Hye-gyong]] finished the highest, ranking 15th, with a season's best of 2:30:29. [[Jo Un-ok]] finished 29th and [[Kim Hye-song (runner)|Kim Hye-song]] did not finish the race.
